For the physicians, clinicians, and administrative team of Northwest Permanente (NWP), P.C., our calling and mission go well beyond the walls of Kaiser Permanente. For these nearly 80 years in the Northwest, we have worked tirelessly to provide best-in-class care for our patients, individually and at the population level; continually engage with our people in striving to become the best place to work; and serve our communities to foster wellness and total health.

As the world’s first physician-led medical group to be certified as a B Corp, we, as a company, are affirmed in our core value of using “business as a force for good,” of being committed to our people and patients and members, and to the planet, balancing prosperity and purpose. In 2018, we were proud to earn B Lab’s “Best for the World” designation for the second year running in the following two categories: “Workers” and “Best Overall.”

Executing on our NWP Corporate Social Responsibility (CSR) Plan in 2018, our impact focused in the areas of food insecurity, education, and the environment. Thank you for joining us in this important work! We are pleased to share some highlights of our work within our community in the <a href="https://nwpermanente.com/wp-content/uploads/2018-NWP_Our-Community-Our-Impact.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">2018 NWP Impact Report</a>.

