<strong><img class="alignnone wp-image-1713" src="https://nwpermanente.com/wp-content/uploads/Poothullil_Antony_M_MD-819x1024.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="188" /></strong>

<strong>Tony Poothullil, MD, Ophthalmology</strong>

<em>What his colleagues say about him: </em>"Dr. Poothullil is a complex and detailed person who cares about the organization, his patients, his colleagues, and his family and manages to make it all work."

<em>From Dr. Poothullil: </em>"What we do as physicians is really special and unique, and it is a privilege that also comes with a lot of responsibility, especially nowadays in this setting. It's a really noble calling, and you're not in it alone — you've got amazing team members and partners, colleagues to call on all the time. That's something I'm constantly reminded of working at a place like Northwest Perm."

