<strong>Jennifer Rupert, MD, Obstetrics and Gynecology</strong>

<em>What her colleagues say about her: </em>"Dr. Rupert works tirelessly at identifying opportunities to recognize the achievements of her peers and staff. She exemplifies Permanente Medicine in the way she seeks to improve herself and our care delivery system."

<em>From Dr. Rupert: </em>"I am humbled and honored to accept this award. As a chief in a pandemic, I often hear about things that aren't going well, so it was surprising and meaningful to me to receive this award. Being open to different possibilities in your career allows you to keep growing as a person. Ultimately, I chose medicine as a career because I wanted to be challenged and not get bored, and I will say that has been the case, especially this year. It is rewarding to be able to work towards meeting a challenge and mostly succeeding, always having something to strive towards."

