<strong>Eric Poolman, MD, Hospital Medicine</strong>

<em>What his colleagues say about him: </em>"Dr. Poolman is not afraid of hard work, or the unknown. His leadership during this pandemic has been so inspiring. He has gone above and beyond — he is always willing to listen and learn. He is thoughtful in his responses, and it's obvious he cares."

<em>From Dr. Poolman: </em>"Sophomore year in college my dad asked me what I wanted to do. Was I going to be a doctor? He would ask, "What are you studying biology for?" I said, "No, I am not going to be a doctor." Looking back, why would I want to spend all my time with smart, dedicated, compassionate people? To be recognized by people I respect, to do something I love to do, is wonderful. I am going to be 47 years old receiving this award, the same age my dad was 25 years ago when he passed away from HIV so he never knew I became a doctor. He would be happy that I am happy, and that I am spending my time with a team I love, getting people through a viral pandemic."

